  <!-- ABOUT CREEK COUNTY -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: white;">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">About Creek County, Oklahoma</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">Creek County is located in northeastern Oklahoma with a population of approximately 72,930 residents as of the 2020 Census. The county seat is Sapulpa, a city of roughly 21,000 people located just southwest of Tulsa along historic Route 66. Creek County covers 956 square miles and is named after the Muscogee (Creek) Nation, which has a significant historical presence in the area.</p>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">Major communities in Creek County include Sapulpa, Bristow, Drumright, Kellyville, Kiefer, Glenpool, Depew, Mannford, Oilton, Mounds, and Slick. The county's proximity to Tulsa means a higher volume of arrests and bond activity than many rural Oklahoma counties. Whether the arrest occurs during a traffic stop on the Turner Turnpike, at a local event, or anywhere within the Creek County Sheriff's patrol area, Angel Bail Bonds can help secure a fast release.</p>

      <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;">How Far Is Creek County from Stillwater?</h3>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-700); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>The Creek County Justice Center in Sapulpa is approximately 60 miles from Stillwater, a drive of about 55 to 70 minutes via US-412 West and US-75 South. Angel Bail Bonds handles Creek County bonds regularly and can coordinate posting remotely by phone, so you may not need to drive to Sapulpa at all.</strong></p>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">Creek County is within our regular service area. In many cases, we can complete the entire bail bond process over the phone — you provide the inmate's information and payment, and we handle the rest directly with the Creek County Justice Center.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
