        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);"><summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How much does a bail bond cost in Creek County?</summary><p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Oklahoma bail bond premiums are regulated by state law. Angel Bail Bonds offers competitive rates with multiple payment options: cash, Visa, Mastercard, Zelle, Venmo, and financing for qualifying clients. Call (405) 614-3000 for a free quote.</p></details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);"><summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How long does release from Creek County Justice Center take?</summary><p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">After Angel Bail Bonds posts the bond, most defendants are released within 2-4 hours. The facility processes about 4,500 inmates annually. Actual release time depends on staffing, time of day, and booking volume.</p></details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);"><summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">When are Creek County arraignments?</summary><p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Arraignments are held at 9:00 AM at the Creek County Courthouse, 222 E. Dewey St, Suite 201, Sapulpa, OK 74066. Call the Court Clerk at (918) 227-2525 for specific docket dates.</p></details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);"><summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">Can I post bail from Stillwater for a Creek County arrest?</summary><p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Yes. Angel Bail Bonds is based in Stillwater, about 60 miles from the Creek County Justice Center. We can handle the entire process remotely by phone.</p></details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);"><summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">Does Angel Bail Bonds serve Bristow, Drumright, and Kellyville?</summary><p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Yes. We serve every community in Creek County, including Sapulpa, Bristow, Drumright, Kellyville, Kiefer, Glenpool, Depew, Mannford, Oilton, Mounds, and Slick.</p></details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);"><summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">What payment methods are accepted for Creek County bail bonds?</summary><p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Angel Bail Bonds accepts cash, Visa, Mastercard, Zelle, and Venmo. We also offer financing plans for clients who qualify. Call (405) 614-3000 to discuss payment options.</p></details>
      </div>
